    "body": "@alexandraB99 I've updated the issue title to match what's still needed.\r\n\r\nThe release process is somewhat of a manual process at the moment, consisting of:\r\n\r\n1. Generate changelog based on git commits starting from last tag using `clog`\r\n2. Create release commit that cuts the next version\r\n3. Create a signed tag of `vx.y.z` (e.g. `v0.21.0`) and put the release notes of that version into the signed tag message\r\n4. Push commit incl. its newly created tag to github\r\n5. Go to GitHub Releases and draft a new release based on the newly created tag. The release nodes go into the release description\r\n\r\nMany of these things can be automated, probably even everything using a combination of some script and possibly GitHub actions.\r\n\r\nThe first step would be to take steps 1) - 4) automate them with something like a `release.sh` file. ",
